description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen within the patient blood management team at the Royal Cornwall Hospital. We are looking for a committed experienced and enthusiastic nurse to work with and support the wider multidisciplinary team and who can also lead and autonomously manage their own workload including nurse-led outpatient clinics and assessments. Applicants will be expected to have considerable clinical skills, supported by relevant qualifications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Patient Blood Management Team have a wide and varied patient group and receive referrals from community and in patient teams and work closely with the haematology department. There will be a requirement for the successful candidate to lead and contribute to education, clinical governance, risk management, research, training and audit. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;A post-registration qualification in transfusion would be desirable. A nurse prescribing qualification (or commitment to undertake) is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This role is Full Time 37.5 hours per week.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sarah Caskey - Clinical Matron Cancer Services on Tel: 01872 253842. Or email: sarah.caskey@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
